projects.title: WordLike Playground
projects.body: Node, Express, and React web application designed to gameify Quill's Wordlike synonym game by enabling a two player mode. Winner of the Quill Prize and third place at Big Think Hackathon 2016.

projects.title: OkayVacay
projects.body: A Ruby On Rails and React web application designed to help the user find the cheapest options for travel avaliable in their budget and aligned with their interests. Created at Launch Hackathon 2016; hosted on Heroku and uses the Expedia API.

projects.title: Planit
projects.body: A Ruby on Rails and Javascript (JQuery) web application designed to help users coordinate between friends and plan a travel itinerary. Created for CS169, Software Engineering; hosted on Heroku and uses the Google Maps API.

projects.title: CookPad
projects.body: A Node.js, Express, and React web application enabling the user to write recipes and browse the most popular recipes calculated by user votes.
